<section>
  <h2>📚 Course Modules</h2>

  <div class="grid">

    <div>
      <h3>🗄️ Module 1: Oracle SQL Basics</h3>
      <p>Learn RDBMS fundamentals, joins, constraints, group functions, ranking functions, and SQL commands.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>❄️ Module 2–6: Snowflake Core</h3>
      <p>Explore architecture, roles/users, warehouses, database objects, and storage concepts.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>⏳ Module 7–8: Time Travel & Cloning</h3>
      <p>Understand data recovery using Time Travel and Zero Copy Cloning techniques.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>📥 Module 9–13: Data Loading</h3>
      <p>Load structured and semi-structured data using Snowpipe, AWS, and staging methods.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>⚙️ Module 14–18: Advanced Snowflake</h3>
      <p>Learn streams, SCDs, performance tuning, masking policies, and advanced functions.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>🔄 Module 20–26: DBT</h3>
      <p>Build transformations, models, testing, macros, snapshots, and GitHub integration.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>☁️ Module 27: Azure Data Factory</h3>
      <p>Create pipelines to load data from Azure Blob Storage into Snowflake.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3>🚀 Module 28: Real-Time Project</h3>
      <p>Develop a full end-to-end data pipeline using Snowflake, DBT, and ADF.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>🎯 Learning Outcomes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Configure and manage Snowflake environments</li>
    <li>Load structured and semi-structured data</li>
    <li>Implement CDC using Streams and Tasks</li>
    <li>Build DBT pipelines with testing</li>
    <li>Create ADF pipelines for cloud data movement</li>
    <li>Perform performance tuning and cost optimization</li>
  </ul>
</section>

